title: For Sale:  NIB Beretta Pico 380
postcontent: Pico - The Most Concealable .380 for Personal Defense and Home Protection At only 18mm wide, the Pico is the thinnest .380 semiauto handgun on the market, making it a best in class for concealed carry and home defense.Besides being light, small and concealable, it offers easy use, adjustable sights, an ultra-reliable low-recoil mechanism and a tough, durable finish that--with proper care--will give you a virtual lifetime of service. Comfortable to Conceal and Carry Weighing only 11.5oz unloaded, this double-action-only (DAO) pistol is comfortable and unobtrusive to carry, no matter your preferred mode. The Pico's flat profile and snag-free lines make it perfect in a pocket holster, while its smooth sides and controls also make it ideal for inside-the-waistband carry--coupled with its extra-durable stainless-steel/polymer construction that is highly sweat-resistant. It will literally disappear even in a small purse, while thanks to its flowing design it will always be easy to draw from concealment when every second counts. Soft-recoiling and Absolutely Reliable The Pico is soft-recoiling and makes target recovery lightning-quick after every shot, thanks to its minimal barrel tilt. This feature also makes feeding utterly reliable, even with more open hollowpoint designs or the hotter .380 commercial loads. This means that when you need it for concealed carry or home protection, the Pico will always deliver the performance you expect of a Beretta. Easy to Disassemble and Customize, Loaded with Features, Made in USA Like its slightly bigger brother the Nano, the Pico is engineered to be easy and intuitive to take apart and reassemble. Its heart is a serialized modular chassis, meaning that the frame can be easily swapped to accommodate the user's preferences. Shipped with a storage case and two 6+1 stainless steel magazines (one flush, one with grip extension), the Pico features adjustable, quick-change sights with no gunsmithing required. It also offers ambidextrous magazine release, as well as a super-low-profile slide-release lever to keep the slide open when desired. The Pico is made in USA and brings all the reliability and quality of Beretta as the leader of a new generation of concealed-carry firearms.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester model 1911 sl
postcontent: This is a classic. It's Winchesters model 1911 nicknamed the Widow maker. There wasn't too many made because of its design of being a barrel charge shotgun. So some thought it would be a good to charge by placing the butt on the ground and pushing down on the barrel. Not a good idea. Thus the nickname widow maker. But to a Winchester collector it was an important shotgun. This was Winchesters first autoloader. It's a 12 gauge and was produced in 1917 so it has reached its 100 year anniversary. This shotgun is still in good working order, but really a nice collection piece. This shotgun is a easy take down.

CZ Custom Protek II 9MM ultimate carry weapon. You’ll be amazed at how smooth this trigger is in both DA and SA. Specs can be found here. https://czcustom.com/new-firearms/cz-pistols-custom/cz-pro-tek-ii-black.html
These are $2050 New from CZ Custom and they are rarely in stock.
The CZ Protek starts life as an aluminum framed CZ 75 compact with rail, or P01. It is then transformed by CZ Custom as an ultimate carry pistol. P01’s are stripped apart and slides are taken to be milled and refinished. Sight cut is made for lo mount tritium night sight. Slide is flatted topped and surface ground to be true. The slide cuts actually lower the sight plane bringing it closer to the barrel. the front of slide is narrowed for easy reholstering. Internals are polished and fitted and trigger job done using CZ Custom comp hammer. Comp hammer is recut. Frames are stripped and dehorned, small parts are dehorned and grips are fitted and blended to the frame. then parts are refinished. Triggers are the excellent. DA is smooth and SA is crisp. DA is in the 7.1 lb range, SA is 3.1 lbs.
This specific Protek has a Heinie 2 dot sight installed, CZ Custom solid firing pin retaining pin, barrel throated to ensure function with conical shaped 147gr rounds and 85C trigger installed to eliminate pinching from stock recurve trigger.
Comes with 2 CZ 14rd magazines with 2 replacement rubber base plates (stock are sharp metal), Box, Accessories, and CZ Custom Test Target
